# Text source must stay LF even on Windows. Shell scripts run under Git Bash and CRLF breaks
# shebangs/here-docs; bin/capture.js is INJECTED into the browser via --init-script and must have a
# frozen, consistent encoding; and pinning these kills phantom CRLF-vs-LF diffs that an editor/tool can
# silently introduce (a build-flow.js edit flipped LF->CRLF before this was pinned), which would hide
# real gate-logic changes in review.
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.js   text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.md   text eol=lf
